-- Caterpillar net rises on sales outside U.S.
-- 
-- Fri Jan 25, 2008 7:48am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/25/us-caterpillar-results-idUSWNAS782120080125

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Caterpillar Inc. ( CAT.N ) said on Friday its profit in the latest quarter rose more than 10 percent due to strong sales outside the United States. 

 The company, the world's largest maker of construction and mining equipment, reported a fourth-quarter profit of $975 million, compared with $882 million last year. Sales rose 10 percent to $12.14 billion. (Reporting by  James B. Kelleher , editing by Phil Berlowitz)